## Planned Enhancements

### 1. Additional Seasons

Current outputs are limited to:

* Breeding-season abundance
* Resident-season abundance (for non-migratory species)

Future versions may include:

* Spring migration
* Fall migration
* Non-breeding / winter abundance

### 2. eBird Raw Data Summaries

Future releases will incorporate raw eBird observations and survey effort summaries alongside BAM survey information.

This will provide:

* Additional evidence of occurrence
* Improved confidence assessment
* Better representation of survey effort across Canada

### 3. Regional Relative Abundance Scaling

Current abundance categories are derived nationally.

Future releases may additionally calculate categories relative to:

* Bird Conservation Regions (BCRs)
* Provinces and territories
* Other ecological regions

This would allow users to identify locations that are regionally important even when they contribute only a small proportion of the national population.

---

## Intended Use

These products are intended as a screening and prioritization tool for environmental review and impact assessment.

They are not intended to:

* Replace project-specific surveys
* Estimate absolute abundance
* Delineate critical habitat
* Support regulatory decisions without additional context

Outputs should be interpreted alongside species biology, local expertise, survey information, and other available evidence.

